First locate the position of 2026 in the square-spiral grid.

1. Determine the ring (or layer).

   The greatest odd square below 2026 is  
   45² = 2025.  
   Therefore 2026 is the very first number of the next ring, whose side length is 47.  
   That ring has index  

   k = (47 – 1)/2 = 23.

2. Coordinates of 2026.

   Every ring k has its bottom-right corner at (k, –k) and that corner contains  
   (2k+1)².

   For k = 22 the bottom-right corner is (22, –22) with value 45² = 2025.  
   Moving one step to the right begins ring 23, so  

   2026 is at (23, –22).

3. Coordinates of the eight neighbours.

   (x, y) = (23, –22)  
   Neighbours are

        (22, –23)   (23, –23)   (24, –23)
        (22, –22)              (24, –22)
        (22, –21)   (23, –21)   (24, –21)

4. “Number-from-coordinate” formula.

   For a point (x, y) let k = max(|x|, |y|).  
   Put m = (2k+1)²  (value in the bottom-right corner of that ring).

   The offset t (number of steps counter-clockwise from the bottom-right corner) is

        bottom side (y = –k) :          t = k – x
        left   side (x = –k) :          t = 2k + y + k = y + 3k
        top    side (y =  k) :          t = 4k + x + k = x + 5k
        right  side (x =  k) :          t = 6k + k – y = 7k – y

   Then the value at (x, y) is  n = m – t.

5. Compute each neighbour.

   (22, –23): k=23 ⇒ m=2209, bottom side → t=1  ⇒ n = 2209 – 1  = 2208  
   (23, –23): k=23 ⇒ m=2209, bottom-right  → t=0  ⇒ n = 2209  
   (24, –23): k=24 ⇒ m=2401, right side    → t=191 ⇒ n = 2401 –191 = 2210  
   (22, –22): k=22 ⇒ m=2025, bottom-right  → t=0  ⇒ n = 2025  
   (24, –22): k=24 ⇒ m=2401, right side    → t=190 ⇒ n = 2401 –190 = 2211  
   (22, –21): k=22 ⇒ m=2025, right side    → t=175 ⇒ n = 2025 –175 = 1850  
   (23, –21): k=23 ⇒ m=2209, right side    → t=182 ⇒ n = 2209 –182 = 2027  
   (24, –21): k=24 ⇒ m=2401, right side    → t=189 ⇒ n = 2401 –189 = 2212  

6. Sum of the eight numbers
 
        2208 + 2209 + 2210 + 2025 +
        2211 + 1850 + 2027 + 2212 = 16952

Answer: 16952
